DATE)

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><stat>INSERT INTO Crop (crop_id, crop_name, crop_type, plant_date, harvest_date) SELECT 1, 'Tomato', 'Vegetable', '2022-01-01', '2022-03-01'</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><stat>INSERT INTO Field (field_id, field_name, area, soil_type, crop_id) SELECT 1, 'Field A', 10.5, 'Clay', 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE Crop (crop_id INT PRIMARY KEY, crop_name VARCHAR(255), crop_type VARCHAR(255), plant_date DATE, harvest_date DATE)

CREATE TABLE Field (field_id INT PRIMARY KEY, field_name VARCHAR(255), area FLOAT, soil_type VARCHAR(255), crop_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (crop_id) REFERENCES Crop(crop_id))

CREATE TABLE IrrigationSystem (system_id INT PRIMARY KEY, system_type VARCHAR(255), capacity FLOAT, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))

CREATE TABLE WeatherSensor (sensor_id INT PRIMARY KEY, location VARCHAR(255), sensor_type VARCHAR(255), field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))</t><stat>insert into weathersensor (sensor_id, location, sensor_type, field_id) select 1, 'sensor a', 'temperature', 1</stat><divider><t>CREATE TABLE CropHealth (health_id INT PRIMARY KEY, health_status VARCHAR(255), timestamp TIMESTAMP, field_id INT, FOREIGN KEY (field_id) REFERENCES Field(field_id))
